A former Commissioner for Agriculture and Natural Resources in Delta State, Joe Utomi, is dead. He slumped and died in Asaba, the state capital on Friday. Utomi hailed from Ubulu-Uku in Aniocha South Local Government Area of the state. He served under Governor Ifeanyi Okowa during his first term in office. President of Ubulu-Uku Development Union and close ally of the late politician, Jones Ofunne, has confirmed the death. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.